    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "And the `file_finder` could be implemented fairly easily as well:\n\n```\nimport os\nimport sys\nfrom IPython.utils.path import filefind\n\ndef find_in_pythonpath(filename):\n    try:\n        path_dirs = ['.'] + os.environ['PYTHONPATH'].split(':')\n    except:\n        path_dirs = ['.']\n    return filefind(filename, path_dirs)\n\ndef find_in_syspath(filename):\n    return filefind(filename, sys.path)\n```\n\nI'm not convinced of the merits of this request.  `python` won't search `sys.path` (or `$PYTHONPATH`) when using `execfile`.  And `%run` is essentially a smarter version of `execfile`.\n"
  },
